title: Nightly compiler panic on using Self with associated type in type alias

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-nightly
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from stable to nightly.

labels.name: A-associated-items
labels.description: Area: Associated items such as associated types and consts.

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
## Description

The `nightly` compiler panics when using `Self` in a type alias along with an associated type. This does not happen on `stable` or `beta`.

Code snippet:
```
type Target = Self::Target;
```
[Playground Link](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=5130b3b8d9685d5333ddd3a2459bf18d)
